WEBVTT

00:27.259 --> 00:29.562
I'm normal.

00:29.594 --> 00:30.762
I'm like everybody else.

00:30.795 --> 00:33.265
I'm normal.
I'm a regular kid.

00:33.298 --> 00:34.466
I'm normal.

00:34.500 --> 00:36.201
I'm a regular kid.
I'm normal.

00:36.234 --> 00:37.536
I'm a regular kid. I'm normal.

00:37.570 --> 00:39.271
Regular kid...

00:39.304 --> 00:41.341
I'm just like everyone else.

00:50.149 --> 00:52.384
I'm...

00:52.417 --> 00:54.554
I'm a normal kid, and...

00:56.822 --> 00:59.258
...I'll be strong.

01:27.186 --> 01:29.822
It's called
the Dragon's Dilemma,

01:29.855 --> 01:33.192
and the dilemma the Dragon has

01:33.224 --> 01:36.695
is whether to send you plunging
down 200 feet to the ground

01:36.728 --> 01:39.364
or up 200 feet in the air.

01:40.365 --> 01:42.534
Are you listening to me?

01:42.567 --> 01:44.469
I want to go home.

01:44.503 --> 01:47.674
It's my birthday... I should
decide what I get to do.

01:49.441 --> 01:51.811
No. You can't. You...

01:51.843 --> 01:55.413
Paul, you spend enough time
alone at home as it is.

01:57.349 --> 01:59.519
- Paul, I just spent five dollars on this.
- Hey, Paul.

01:59.552 --> 02:00.620
Is that you?

02:00.653 --> 02:02.421
How you doing, buddy?

02:02.453 --> 02:04.623
- You know these guys?
- Yeah, we're his friends.

02:04.656 --> 02:05.625
Oh. Hey.

02:05.658 --> 02:07.293
- You're his dad, right?
- Yeah.

02:07.325 --> 02:08.894
Huh.

02:08.927 --> 02:11.563
- So, how'd it feel?
- How'd what feel?

02:11.597 --> 02:13.199
When you screwed that dog
and made him.

02:17.703 --> 02:20.239
Tell me their names.

02:20.271 --> 02:22.774
They don't have names.

02:22.807 --> 02:24.810
Step right up...

02:29.414 --> 02:30.849
Uh...

02:30.883 --> 02:34.854
I was gonna give you this
tonight, but instead...

02:34.887 --> 02:36.489
Step right up!

02:36.521 --> 02:38.223
Happy birthday.

02:39.592 --> 02:41.427
Open it.

02:54.006 --> 02:56.474
Do you like it?

02:56.508 --> 02:58.912
You like it?

03:01.379 --> 03:03.248
Hey, don't worry
about those kids, okay?

03:03.282 --> 03:04.517
Just forget about 'em.

03:04.550 --> 03:06.285
You ready?

03:06.318 --> 03:07.554
Okay.

03:11.723 --> 03:13.592
- Okay, this is it.
- Dad, I don't want...

03:13.626 --> 03:15.260
Dad, I don't want to do this.

03:15.294 --> 03:17.362
Now, what do you do
when people make a comment?

03:17.395 --> 03:19.264
- Yeah, but you said...
- What do you do?

03:19.298 --> 03:20.733
- Dig-Dignity.
- Right, dignity.

03:20.765 --> 03:22.701
Show some dignity.
Stand up straight,

03:22.735 --> 03:25.237
you speak loud, and... I
can't make this clear enough...

03:25.270 --> 03:26.738
Paul, you don't run.

03:26.771 --> 03:28.473
Something happens,
you get nervous,

03:28.507 --> 03:30.408
you stay right where you are...

03:30.442 --> 03:32.478
and you don't run.

03:32.510 --> 03:33.679
Okay?

03:33.711 --> 03:36.548
Now take off your mask.

03:48.593 --> 03:49.929
Great.

03:53.564 --> 03:55.567
Dignity. Right?

03:55.600 --> 03:57.603
Stand up straight.

03:58.736 --> 04:00.740
Get on line.
You got this.

04:17.889 --> 04:19.457
I'll be strong.

04:19.490 --> 04:20.959
I'm a regular kid.
I'm normal.

04:20.992 --> 04:22.295
- Regular kid.
- Tickets.

04:22.327 --> 04:24.729
Tickets. Tickets. Tickets.

04:27.833 --> 04:30.603
You got a ticket?

04:30.636 --> 04:32.305
So, how'd it feel?

04:32.338 --> 04:34.507
When you screwed that dog
and made him?

04:37.576 --> 04:39.579
Paul! Paul!

04:59.732 --> 05:01.000
Where's your dad now, buddy?

05:01.033 --> 05:02.902
I'll bet he's
back at the pound!

05:02.935 --> 05:04.437
He's probably fingering
your mother

05:04.470 --> 05:06.005
before they put her to sleep!

05:06.038 --> 05:07.907
My mom's not a dog!

05:07.939 --> 05:11.009
- Yeah? You ever met her?
- Shut up!

05:11.043 --> 05:13.778
Make me!

05:13.812 --> 05:15.413
Dog!

05:15.447 --> 05:18.617
Why don't you bark for us?

05:18.649 --> 05:20.819
Go on, bark!

05:20.853 --> 05:22.355
You heard him!

05:22.387 --> 05:24.823
- Bark!
- Bark for us, boy!

05:24.857 --> 05:26.992
He said bark!

05:27.024 --> 05:28.626
- Bark!
- Only thing you're good at!

05:28.660 --> 05:29.995
Bark, you idiot!

05:30.028 --> 05:31.430
Come on, we know you can do it!

05:31.463 --> 05:32.531
Spit it out!

05:32.564 --> 05:33.799
Bark, dog!

05:51.083 --> 05:53.386
I'm gonna go to my room.

05:59.557 --> 06:03.396
Look, I know you had
a rough day,

06:03.428 --> 06:06.031
but I really want
to show you something.

06:14.038 --> 06:18.543
Every child is
like a beautiful musical note.

06:18.576 --> 06:21.713
It's just that some notes are
more unique than other notes.

06:21.747 --> 06:24.182
What we like to do
is take those musical notes

06:24.216 --> 06:26.886
and put them together
and make a song.

06:26.918 --> 06:29.822
And we call that song
Bishop Griffin.

06:29.855 --> 06:31.657
Here at Bishop Griffin,

06:31.689 --> 06:34.826
we believe that a well-rounded
education comes from...

06:34.860 --> 06:37.730
embracing the differences
of those around us

06:37.762 --> 06:40.498
while creating a safe,
inclusive environment

06:40.531 --> 06:43.601
to learn, play and grow.

06:43.634 --> 06:45.805
Oh! Nice shot there, Byron.

06:47.172 --> 06:49.608
Every child has a right to be educated.

06:49.641 --> 06:52.578
Every child has a right
to be respected.

06:52.610 --> 06:56.081
Every child has
a right to be loved.

06:56.113 --> 06:57.750
Nice work there, buddy.

06:57.783 --> 06:59.951
- Who's that?
- Um, Iron Man.

06:59.985 --> 07:01.721
That's exactly what I thought.

07:03.922 --> 07:06.892
A griffin is not
a lion nor eagle.

07:06.925 --> 07:10.663
A griffin is
something else entirely.

07:10.696 --> 07:13.833
At Bishop Griffin's, we take
inspiration from the griffin.

07:13.865 --> 07:17.536
And together we teach
one another how to fly.

07:20.105 --> 07:21.641
Okay.

07:22.641 --> 07:24.110
What do you think?

07:28.247 --> 07:30.749
I think that if you send me
to this school,

07:30.781 --> 07:32.685
I will burn it to the ground.

07:32.718 --> 07:34.987
Yeah, right. Okay,

07:35.019 --> 07:37.956
I have one last
birthday present for you.

07:39.858 --> 07:42.093
Check this out.

07:43.127 --> 07:44.997
Try it on.

07:46.163 --> 07:47.933
Give it a shot.

07:49.166 --> 07:51.002
Paul.

08:20.031 --> 08:22.868
"To Paul, from Mom."

09:02.640 --> 09:04.543
Do you know
where this came from?

09:07.712 --> 09:08.880
Wow.

09:08.913 --> 09:10.649
Wow, look at you.
You look great.

09:10.682 --> 09:12.951
Look out, ladies.
James Bond over here.

09:12.985 --> 09:14.353
You don't know
where this came from?

09:14.385 --> 09:17.822
Oh, that? Yeah, that,
uh, came this afternoon.

09:17.855 --> 09:19.924
What was in it?

09:19.957 --> 09:21.225
Nothing.

09:21.259 --> 09:23.228
I can't get over
how great you look.

09:23.260 --> 09:25.096
- You look...
- I look like a Build-A-Bear.

09:25.129 --> 09:26.764
No, you don't.

09:26.798 --> 09:29.033
Yeah, I got a good feeling
about this school.

09:29.067 --> 09:30.168
I got a good...

09:30.201 --> 09:32.737
I got a good feeling.

09:32.770 --> 09:34.740
It's gonna be
a terrific opportunity

09:34.773 --> 09:36.609
for you
to meet people like you.

09:36.642 --> 09:38.310
I don't want to meet
people like me.

09:38.342 --> 09:40.078
Why not?

09:41.113 --> 09:43.583
Because I hate me.

09:48.653 --> 09:51.823
I, uh, I don't know
what to tell you, Paul.

09:51.856 --> 09:53.725
All right,
what do you want me to do?

09:53.759 --> 09:56.195
I don't know what to do.

09:56.227 --> 09:58.329
I-I can't get you
to stick up for yourself.

09:58.363 --> 09:59.965
I can't get you
to meet friends.

09:59.998 --> 10:01.867
I can't get you to take off
that stupid mask.

10:01.899 --> 10:03.802
What do you want me to do?
Help me out.

10:03.835 --> 10:05.304
Mom wouldn't make me go
to this school.

10:05.336 --> 10:06.771
What?

10:06.804 --> 10:08.907
- Mom...
- Mom?

10:10.908 --> 10:13.111
Yeah, well, if she cared
so much about you,

10:13.144 --> 10:14.145
why'd she leave?

10:19.017 --> 10:21.820
I'm sorry.

10:21.852 --> 10:25.323
Paul, I'm sorry. I shouldn't
have said that, okay?

10:25.356 --> 10:27.192
- I didn't mean that. Come on, let's eat.
- Don't touch me.

10:29.094 --> 10:31.930
Paul, I said I was sor...
Ow!

10:31.962 --> 10:33.399
You just bit me!

10:48.480 --> 10:49.947
Paul?

10:49.980 --> 10:52.183
Paul, open up. Come on.

10:52.216 --> 10:53.718
Come on, pal.

10:53.751 --> 10:55.687
I'm sorry, okay?
I said I was sorry.

10:55.721 --> 10:57.755
I don't want to talk
about her anymore, okay?

10:57.788 --> 10:59.057
I'm sorry I said that, but...

11:00.725 --> 11:02.126
...I don't want
to talk about her,

11:02.159 --> 11:03.961
and I don't think
you should think about her.

11:15.273 --> 11:17.043
Paul, please open the door?

11:25.317 --> 11:27.086
There are some...

11:27.119 --> 11:29.754
There are some things that
I've always wanted to ask you.

11:32.256 --> 11:35.393
You were there
when I was born, obviously.

11:37.028 --> 11:39.031
And then you ran away.

11:40.331 --> 11:42.367
Was it easy?

11:44.503 --> 11:46.706
Did it hurt?

11:51.042 --> 11:53.045
Have you ever looked back?

11:59.049 --> 12:00.485
Fuck!

12:44.395 --> 12:46.865
♪ Have you ever been lonely? ♪

12:48.533 --> 12:50.802
♪ Have you ever been blue? ♪

12:51.836 --> 12:53.938
Mm-mm.

12:53.971 --> 12:56.542
♪ Have you ever loved
someone... ♪

13:00.378 --> 13:01.847
Excuse me.

13:01.879 --> 13:04.383
Where in the hell
did you come from?

13:04.416 --> 13:06.385
Do you know how
to get to Pennsylvania?

13:06.418 --> 13:08.086
You'll have to speak up, kid.

13:08.119 --> 13:10.088
I have a bum ear.

13:10.120 --> 13:12.090
Do you know how
to get to Pennsylvania?

13:12.123 --> 13:14.225
- Pencil what?
- Pennsylvania.

13:14.259 --> 13:16.294
What's your name?

13:16.327 --> 13:18.197
I don't know.

13:18.230 --> 13:20.865
You don't know your name, hmm?

13:20.899 --> 13:22.868
All right.

13:22.900 --> 13:26.572
You have parents,
boy with no name?

13:26.605 --> 13:28.440
No.

13:28.472 --> 13:31.909
So, what, you just grew out
of the ground fully formed?

13:31.942 --> 13:34.913
♪ Take me back
in your heart... ♪

13:34.946 --> 13:36.915
What are you hiding...

13:36.947 --> 13:38.951
behind there, hmm?

13:40.018 --> 13:42.187
Nothing.

13:42.220 --> 13:45.324
Hey. It's okay.

13:45.356 --> 13:49.026
There's nothing
to be ashamed of here.

13:49.059 --> 13:50.895
Look around you, hmm?

13:50.928 --> 13:54.365
♪ I've been through,
then you'd know... ♪

13:54.399 --> 13:56.934
We welcome all comers.

13:56.967 --> 14:00.304
♪ Have you ever been lonely? ♪

14:00.337 --> 14:03.140
So... show me.

14:03.173 --> 14:05.209
♪ Have you ever been blue? ♪

14:05.243 --> 14:08.213
I won't look. Okay?

14:23.294 --> 14:25.496
Well.

14:29.366 --> 14:31.168
♪ If you knew... ♪

14:31.201 --> 14:33.337
That is some...

14:33.370 --> 14:35.307
kind of beautiful.

14:35.340 --> 14:39.677
♪ Then you'd know why
I ask you... ♪

14:39.711 --> 14:42.947
My name is Mr. Silk.

14:42.980 --> 14:46.652
And I think we should talk.

14:48.485 --> 14:50.088
After you.

14:52.624 --> 14:54.659
Make yourself at home.

14:57.729 --> 14:59.364
Ants.

14:59.397 --> 15:01.700
You got to watch out.

15:01.732 --> 15:04.335
You stare at 'em long enough,
it starts to feel

15:04.369 --> 15:07.406
like they're crawling around
inside your bloodstream.

15:09.474 --> 15:12.277
- Smoke?
- No. Thank you.

15:12.309 --> 15:14.679
So...

15:14.712 --> 15:17.448
do you like my carnival?

15:17.481 --> 15:19.183
Don't lie.

15:19.216 --> 15:20.619
I see it as it is.

15:20.652 --> 15:22.321
Hmm.

15:22.354 --> 15:24.556
Wasn't always that way.

15:24.589 --> 15:26.325
This little cluster of

15:26.357 --> 15:29.627
tilt-a-whirls
and guess-your-weights.

15:29.660 --> 15:32.496
She was my baby.

15:32.529 --> 15:36.033
Best cotton candy
in the tristate area.

15:36.067 --> 15:37.568
Hmm?

15:37.601 --> 15:39.938
Here's to you.

15:43.741 --> 15:45.743
Ah.

15:45.777 --> 15:48.113
Anyway, you know kids.

15:48.145 --> 15:51.750
Start out so damn cute,
but you come home one day,

15:51.783 --> 15:54.986
you barely even recognize them.

15:55.019 --> 15:56.454
I tell you,

15:56.488 --> 16:01.059
the transitory
entertainment business

16:01.091 --> 16:03.194
just isn't what it used to be.

16:03.227 --> 16:05.730
Makes a man feel...

16:07.599 --> 16:09.267
...very old.

16:13.571 --> 16:15.173
You get my meaning?

16:18.143 --> 16:19.511
I'd like to offer you

16:19.543 --> 16:22.380
a partnership, and with it,

16:22.413 --> 16:25.750
enough money
to get to Pennsylvania

16:25.783 --> 16:27.986
ten times over.

16:35.059 --> 16:37.061
What would I have to do?

16:37.095 --> 16:38.629
Do?

16:38.663 --> 16:42.167
Just... be yourself.

16:42.200 --> 16:44.302
So what do you say?

16:44.335 --> 16:46.171
Do we have ourselves a deal?

16:55.346 --> 16:56.648
Hi.

16:56.681 --> 16:59.051
Detective Pollok. We spoke?

17:00.652 --> 17:03.155
So take me through
what happened again.

17:03.187 --> 17:04.522
Uh...

17:04.556 --> 17:06.658
Oh, uh, I told you

17:06.691 --> 17:09.094
we had an argument, and, uh...

17:13.230 --> 17:14.633
And he bit me.

17:14.665 --> 17:16.801
- He bit you?
- Yeah.

17:16.835 --> 17:18.604
And then he left.

17:23.607 --> 17:26.377
Oh, uh, that's his hair.
Sorry.

17:27.811 --> 17:30.581
Uh, it's just all over.
It's...

17:30.615 --> 17:32.384
not a big deal.
Excuse me.

17:34.486 --> 17:36.655
Does he bite you often?

17:36.688 --> 17:40.225
No. No, he doesn't.

17:40.258 --> 17:42.561
But he's got a temper.
He was angry?

17:43.862 --> 17:45.564
No, he's a good kid.

17:45.596 --> 17:47.298
But he bit you?

17:48.599 --> 17:51.102
Do you want to see his room?

17:51.135 --> 17:54.405
Do you have any current photos?

17:54.439 --> 17:56.675
No, I don't.

17:56.708 --> 18:00.412
He, uh... he doesn't like
his... picture taken.

18:00.444 --> 18:02.379
Not one?

18:02.413 --> 18:04.415
What teenager doesn't like
his picture taken?

18:04.449 --> 18:06.218
He doesn't.

18:09.287 --> 18:11.155
When do I get the money?

18:11.189 --> 18:13.592
You're an eager one, huh?

18:13.625 --> 18:17.194
First you do the work,
then you get the paycheck.

18:17.228 --> 18:20.731
So, show me what you got.

18:20.765 --> 18:23.168
Take off your shirt.

18:24.769 --> 18:26.371
No.

18:27.538 --> 18:29.840
Well, here's what's...

18:29.874 --> 18:31.675
gonna happen.

18:31.709 --> 18:35.413
There's gonna be a line
of folks out here.

18:35.445 --> 18:38.750
And now,
for the beguiling, bizarre.

18:38.782 --> 18:43.320
Come see the dangerous Dog Boy.

18:43.354 --> 18:46.423
They come in.

18:46.457 --> 18:47.826
They look at you.

18:47.858 --> 18:49.627
You look at them.

18:49.661 --> 18:53.298
Eye contact.
You do your thing.

18:53.330 --> 18:55.766
- What thing?
- The thing where you're you.

18:55.799 --> 19:00.239
Oh, one more thing.
Do you have a nut allergy?

19:02.773 --> 19:05.376
I think
I'll call it "Wolf Mash."

19:05.410 --> 19:10.415
Look, I'm not hiring you
for your sunny disposition.

19:10.448 --> 19:12.951
And last I heard,
you can't buy a bus ticket

19:12.983 --> 19:15.287
with a wallet full
of principles.

19:15.319 --> 19:17.422
There goes Pennsylvania.

19:17.454 --> 19:19.924
The horror.
The horror of this child.

19:19.958 --> 19:22.361
Folks like you and me.

19:23.461 --> 19:25.797
We give the people
what they want.

19:25.829 --> 19:27.731
Come over here.
Come over here!

19:27.765 --> 19:29.901
What they fear.

19:29.933 --> 19:32.570
There's a power in that.

19:34.305 --> 19:36.408
I don't think I want
to do this anymore.

19:42.512 --> 19:44.515
So go home.

19:44.548 --> 19:48.420
Go back
wherever it is you came from.

19:48.452 --> 19:50.454
Get the hell out of here!

19:51.489 --> 19:52.924
Leave!

19:57.428 --> 19:58.763
Get ready

19:58.796 --> 20:00.632
to scream!

20:02.700 --> 20:05.737
Only five dollars.

20:05.769 --> 20:07.506
The horror of this child!

20:11.509 --> 20:14.378
Attaboy.

20:23.887 --> 20:25.890
Clowns!

20:26.891 --> 20:29.427
Tonight...

20:29.460 --> 20:30.862
we dance!

20:30.894 --> 20:33.397
Ha-ha! Yes!

20:36.901 --> 20:39.971
Hey, drink up, you...

20:40.003 --> 20:41.472
marauders...

20:41.506 --> 20:43.041
pirates.

20:43.074 --> 20:47.379
I'd say that we had
a damn productive day, huh?

20:47.412 --> 20:50.281
Yeah!

20:50.315 --> 20:51.682
Where's my money?

20:51.715 --> 20:54.418
Whoa, fella!

20:54.451 --> 20:56.621
So you had a hard day
at the office.

20:56.653 --> 20:59.758
I see no reason
why we should terminate

20:59.790 --> 21:02.326
our working relationship.

21:02.359 --> 21:04.561
Do you?

21:04.595 --> 21:06.664
- The money.
- Patience, boy.

21:06.698 --> 21:08.733
This is not a one-shot deal.

21:08.766 --> 21:10.669
We're just getting started.

21:10.701 --> 21:12.804
Why don't you hop
on this sucker?

21:12.836 --> 21:14.538
- Give it a spin.
- Yeah. - Come on.

21:14.571 --> 21:16.707
Join the family.

21:16.740 --> 21:20.478
Let's ride!

21:20.510 --> 21:22.980
Come on, boy with no name!

21:23.013 --> 21:24.415
Have some fun!

21:24.449 --> 21:26.051
Come on!

21:26.084 --> 21:27.585
Let your hair down!

21:27.617 --> 21:29.320
Ha-ha!

21:29.354 --> 21:30.922
God, yes!

21:30.954 --> 21:34.525
I wish you could see it
as it once was.

21:34.558 --> 21:36.894
Oh, but we built
something special.

21:36.928 --> 21:39.497
Paradise... paradise!

21:39.529 --> 21:42.567
I close my eyes
and I can still hear

21:42.599 --> 21:45.436
the children's laughter.

21:55.445 --> 21:57.682
Where did it all go?

22:29.113 --> 22:30.815
Get him. Get him!

22:30.847 --> 22:32.884
Violence!

22:36.586 --> 22:38.655
No.

22:38.689 --> 22:42.527
No! Save the Dragon!
Don't let it get to the Dragon!

22:42.559 --> 22:44.995
Put out the fire!

22:45.028 --> 22:48.465
My God, no!

22:48.499 --> 22:50.168
Oh, no!

