I'm gonna introduce you
to the Queen.

47:55.271 --> 47:58.508
There she is! The Queen.

47:58.541 --> 48:01.545
Make sure you bow.

48:03.980 --> 48:06.449
Really?

48:06.481 --> 48:07.650
Yep.

48:14.456 --> 48:17.126
This place is amazing.

48:17.159 --> 48:19.161
Yeah. A bunch of kids
jumped off it

48:19.195 --> 48:21.197
in some sort of death pact,
and it's been awesome

48:21.230 --> 48:24.067
- ever since.
- I'm gonna go change.

48:24.099 --> 48:25.601
Suit yourself.

48:26.601 --> 48:29.373
Where's the beer?

48:34.344 --> 48:37.514
She's angry at me
for taking you along.

48:43.353 --> 48:46.556
I knew her before, you know.

48:46.588 --> 48:48.257
When she was
a scrawny little geek

48:48.291 --> 48:51.594
with terrible clothes
and no personality.

48:51.626 --> 48:54.130
She used to not speak to anyone
and then go onstage

48:54.163 --> 48:56.699
and read this awful poetry
about horses.

48:58.701 --> 49:01.505
Don't be mean to her.

49:02.704 --> 49:04.141
Whatever.

49:06.141 --> 49:08.610
She's right, you know.

49:08.643 --> 49:10.179
Running around like this?

49:10.213 --> 49:12.983
It's probably
all gonna end in tears.

49:13.016 --> 49:15.617
Well, it's, um...

49:15.650 --> 49:18.187
At least it's fun, right?

49:18.221 --> 49:20.356
It's not really that fun.

49:20.389 --> 49:23.659
Then why do you do it?

49:23.693 --> 49:27.097
It's probably all my
self-destructive tendencies.

49:31.434 --> 49:33.570
Wouldn't be so bad, you know.

49:33.603 --> 49:35.739
- What?
- Jail.

49:36.773 --> 49:38.274
I mean, in some jails,

49:38.306 --> 49:40.376
I hear they have
an ice cream station.

49:40.409 --> 49:43.078
A library.

49:43.112 --> 49:45.382
Nice beds.

49:45.414 --> 49:47.217
What, you don't have a bed?

49:48.717 --> 49:50.553
Not really.

49:51.586 --> 49:53.255
Why not?

49:53.289 --> 49:56.493
You were asking
about my house before?

49:57.726 --> 49:59.730
You've already been
to my house.

50:02.197 --> 50:04.701
My house is the car, Paul.

50:04.733 --> 50:06.735
Oh.

50:06.768 --> 50:09.005
Chug.

50:14.443 --> 50:17.014
So, what do you want
to do next?

50:22.851 --> 50:24.820
Happy birthday!

50:52.414 --> 50:55.284
This is crazy, huh?

50:56.452 --> 50:58.789
I can't believe
it's all for me.

51:02.625 --> 51:04.327
Why aren't you down there?

51:06.528 --> 51:09.199
It's gonna take forever
to grow back.

51:10.365 --> 51:12.134
I'm sorry.

51:12.168 --> 51:14.170
I mean,
I don't know why we care

51:14.202 --> 51:15.505
so much about hair anyway.

51:15.538 --> 51:17.373
I mean, it's just, like,
these tentacles

51:17.405 --> 51:21.177
that grow out of our skulls,
but...

51:21.210 --> 51:23.179
When I was little,
I used to go in the bathroom

51:23.211 --> 51:25.382
and wrap a towel
around my head, so...

51:27.282 --> 51:29.418
...it's got to mean something.

51:33.755 --> 51:35.257
Are you mad at me?

51:36.659 --> 51:39.695
Well, you did rob, like,
four different stores.

51:39.728 --> 51:41.530
- Yeah.
- But...

51:41.563 --> 51:44.400
I'm glad you get to have
your own party.

51:45.601 --> 51:47.503
Having fun?

51:47.536 --> 51:51.173
Yeah. I have fireworks.

51:51.206 --> 51:52.875
And you don't know
what direction they went in?

51:52.909 --> 51:54.544
I really have no idea.

51:56.311 --> 51:57.547
Showtime, y'all!

52:07.956 --> 52:11.860
God bless
all the stupid children.

52:11.893 --> 52:16.598
I want to dedicate this night
to Paul on his...

52:16.632 --> 52:18.367
How old are you, Paul?

52:18.400 --> 52:19.568
Thirteen.

52:19.601 --> 52:22.271
On his 13th birthday!

52:28.411 --> 52:30.346
Happy birthday.

52:30.378 --> 52:32.414
Make a wish.

52:50.766 --> 52:53.470
- Stop! Police!
- This way! Come on!

53:01.677 --> 53:04.381
Goddamn it, Rose.

53:16.358 --> 53:17.693
Wait.

53:20.929 --> 53:23.332
- What... Why?
- Oh, I lied.

53:23.365 --> 53:24.766
That's definitely not
a water gun.

53:24.800 --> 53:26.469
Shit.

53:26.501 --> 53:29.005
- I think this is my time to punch out.
- What?

53:29.038 --> 53:31.773
- Come on. Getting arrested?
- No, no, no.

53:31.806 --> 53:34.443
We're sticking together
because, um,

53:34.476 --> 53:37.246
- you made me a party, and you can't...
- Paul. Go.

53:37.280 --> 53:39.349
- We should.
- What...?

53:39.382 --> 53:42.652
Wait, wait, wait, Rose, Rose.

53:42.684 --> 53:44.788
What happened to your eye?

53:47.322 --> 53:49.326
Lazy eye.

53:56.565 --> 53:59.235
When you stopped running...

54:00.503 --> 54:03.573
...did you like
where you ended up?

54:07.677 --> 54:10.012
Did you start a new family?

54:13.481 --> 54:15.818
Did you tell 'em about us?

54:31.032 --> 54:33.702
So, here it is as I see it.

54:33.735 --> 54:35.570
We don't have any food,

54:35.603 --> 54:38.573
we're being chased
by the police,

54:38.606 --> 54:40.876
and I left
my nail polish behind.

54:42.878 --> 54:47.417
So... what do we do now?

54:50.418 --> 54:52.422
I know.

55:12.907 --> 55:14.009
Okay.

55:34.028 --> 55:37.833
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

55:39.168 --> 55:42.872
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

55:44.606 --> 55:47.943
♪ Death, she must have
been your will ♪

55:49.945 --> 55:53.483
♪ A bone beneath
the reaper's veil ♪

55:55.550 --> 56:00.722
♪ With your voice,
my belly sunk ♪

56:00.755 --> 56:06.094
♪ And I began
to feel so drunk ♪

56:06.128 --> 56:12.068
♪ Candle, candle on my clock ♪

56:12.101 --> 56:14.670
♪ Oh, Lord,
I must have heard you ♪

56:14.702 --> 56:17.038
♪ Knock me out of bed ♪

56:17.072 --> 56:20.476
♪ As the flames
licked my head ♪

56:20.509 --> 56:23.780
♪ And my lungs
filled up black ♪

56:23.813 --> 56:26.983
♪ In their tiny little shack ♪

56:27.016 --> 56:29.684
♪ It was real and I repent ♪

56:29.717 --> 56:32.888
♪ All those messages you sent ♪

56:32.922 --> 56:36.425
♪ Clear as day,
but in the night ♪

56:36.458 --> 56:39.728
♪ Oh, I couldn't get it right ♪

56:44.900 --> 56:49.204
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

56:50.606 --> 56:54.944
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

56:56.144 --> 56:58.547
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

57:06.255 --> 57:08.224
♪ Here is a church ♪

57:08.257 --> 57:11.461
♪ And here is a steeple ♪

57:11.494 --> 57:17.200
♪ Open the doors,
there are the people ♪

57:17.233 --> 57:22.672
♪ And all their little hearts
at ease ♪

57:22.704 --> 57:26.875
♪ For another week's disease ♪

57:28.610 --> 57:33.081
♪ And eagle, eagle,
talons scream... ♪

57:33.114 --> 57:35.451
How is it?

57:36.652 --> 57:38.954
♪ I was on the fence... ♪

57:38.987 --> 57:41.123
- Weird.
- Bye!

57:41.155 --> 57:43.625
♪ Down my throat ♪

57:43.659 --> 57:45.961
♪ Into the pit, with my head ♪

57:45.994 --> 57:47.963
♪ Upon the spit ♪

57:47.996 --> 57:51.266
♪ Oh, Reverend, please,
can I chew your ear? ♪

57:51.300 --> 57:54.704
♪ I've become
what I most fear ♪

57:54.737 --> 57:57.974
♪ And I know there's
no such thing as ghosts ♪

57:58.007 --> 58:02.545
♪ But I have seen
the demon host ♪

58:07.148 --> 58:11.186
♪ Ooh... ♪

58:12.186 --> 58:16.692
♪ Ooh... ♪

58:17.893 --> 58:20.896
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh ♪

58:22.831 --> 58:25.835
♪ Oh, whoa, oh, oh. ♪

58:54.362 --> 58:56.298
Hi.

58:56.331 --> 58:59.268
- Hello?
- Uh, I'm sorry to bother you. I just...

59:00.802 --> 59:02.771
I kind of got
a weird question for you.

59:02.804 --> 59:04.973
I-I just wanted to know
if this wrapping paper,

59:05.007 --> 59:07.643
does it look familiar to you?

59:07.675 --> 59:08.978
- No.
- My son is missing,

59:09.010 --> 59:10.679
and he got this package.

59:10.713 --> 59:13.249
Uh, and you have the same...

59:13.282 --> 59:15.251
I don't know what
you're talking about.

59:20.054 --> 59:22.657
Wait a minute. Hey.

59:22.690 --> 59:24.192
I know you.

59:24.226 --> 59:26.663
From the carnival.

59:27.695 --> 59:28.864
Percy?

59:31.900 --> 59:33.735
What are you gonna
do when you see her?

59:33.768 --> 59:36.204
Uh, I guess
I'll just figure it out

59:36.237 --> 59:37.606
when I get there.

59:39.942 --> 59:41.945
Here it is.

59:45.014 --> 59:47.884
Paul, are you sure this is it?

59:50.219 --> 59:53.356
- Yeah.
- 'Cause it looks kind of...

59:53.389 --> 59:56.325
Uh... Okay, um...

59:56.358 --> 1:00:01.197
Is it okay if, um...
you stay out here?

1:00:01.230 --> 1:00:03.733
I think I just...

1:00:03.766 --> 1:00:05.901
think I need to do this alone,
you know?

1:00:05.934 --> 1:00:08.805
- Yeah. Okay.
- Okay.

1:00:11.306 --> 1:00:14.177
Okay.

1:00:23.152 --> 1:00:25.153
Hello?

1:00:32.126 --> 1:00:34.130
Hello?

1:01:02.157 --> 1:01:04.861
Where is he?

1:01:05.893 --> 1:01:07.128
Where the hell's my son?

1:01:07.161 --> 1:01:09.164
I don't know.

1:01:09.197 --> 1:01:11.033
What's this?

1:01:12.166 --> 1:01:14.036
It was just a prank.

1:01:46.501 --> 1:01:48.371
Paul.

1:01:50.105 --> 1:01:52.108
You okay?

1:01:57.012 --> 1:01:59.849
It was all a joke.

1:01:59.882 --> 1:02:03.018
She didn't want to meet me.
She never did. Sh...

1:02:03.050 --> 1:02:05.353
- Paul, let's go outside.
- No, I-I'm...

1:02:05.387 --> 1:02:07.923
I'm not a regular kid. I'm...

1:02:07.956 --> 1:02:11.260
I'm not a-a hero.
I'm-I'm-I'm a freak.

1:02:11.293 --> 1:02:12.894
Paul, you can't say that
about yourself.

1:02:12.927 --> 1:02:15.029
No, we have to be honest
with ourselves, okay?

1:02:15.063 --> 1:02:16.766
We're never honest
with ourselves.

1:02:16.798 --> 1:02:19.335
- I think I'm very honest...
- No, you're not, okay?

1:02:19.367 --> 1:02:21.737
I'm not a hero, and you're not
a girl. You're-you're a boy.

1:02:26.007 --> 1:02:28.343
And nothing we can do
will ever change that.

1:02:31.813 --> 1:02:33.782
You're right.

1:02:33.815 --> 1:02:36.184
You're not a hero.

1:03:25.567 --> 1:03:29.304
Hey there, boy with no name.

1:03:31.039 --> 1:03:34.510
You know, I've been thinking.

1:03:34.543 --> 1:03:39.448
What is it you're trying
to repent for?

1:03:40.481 --> 1:03:42.150
What?

1:03:42.184 --> 1:03:44.586
I'm sure this has been fun,

1:03:44.619 --> 1:03:47.623
running around,
playing pretend,

1:03:47.655 --> 1:03:51.025
looking for, what,
validation, hmm?

1:03:51.059 --> 1:03:52.995
If you try to hurt me again,
I'll burn down more than...

1:03:53.027 --> 1:03:55.330
Don't you dare talk
about burning!

1:04:01.168 --> 1:04:03.071
My apologies.

1:04:04.405 --> 1:04:09.378
What I should be saying is:
congratulations.

1:04:09.411 --> 1:04:14.083
Looks like you finally got
where you needed to be.

1:04:14.115 --> 1:04:17.286
But lest you forget,
boy with no name,

1:04:17.318 --> 1:04:21.190
you've still got a contract
to hold up.

1:04:40.608 --> 1:04:41.610
Silence!

1:04:49.617 --> 1:04:55.123
But I think you're not facing
the reality of your situation.

1:04:56.291 --> 1:04:59.295
No more fairy tales.

1:05:00.695 --> 1:05:04.432
No more make-believe.

1:05:05.733 --> 1:05:10.172
You have a disfiguring
medical condition...

1:05:16.110 --> 1:05:18.579
...that disturbs
the people around you.

1:05:18.612 --> 1:05:21.416
You think you can have a job?

1:05:22.451 --> 1:05:25.454
A wife? Children?

1:05:26.588 --> 1:05:28.423
All you're good for is

1:05:28.456 --> 1:05:32.460
a long stare
and a weak punch line.

1:05:32.494 --> 1:05:33.495
You heard him!

1:05:34.563 --> 1:05:36.164
Why don't you bark for us?

1:05:36.197 --> 1:05:38.466
Son.

1:05:38.500 --> 1:05:41.336
- Go on, bark!
- You're going to die ugly...

1:05:44.438 --> 1:05:45.740
...and unloved.

1:05:49.478 --> 1:05:51.547
You little bast...

1:05:51.579 --> 1:05:52.981
Police!

1:06:33.521 --> 1:06:35.356
Hey.

1:06:35.389 --> 1:06:38.292
Tea.

1:06:38.326 --> 1:06:41.295
How'd you guys find me?

1:06:41.329 --> 1:06:43.565
It was your father, actually.

1:06:43.597 --> 1:06:45.266
Really?

1:06:46.835 --> 1:06:49.038
Uh, am I going to jail, or...?

1:06:49.070 --> 1:06:51.139
Let's take that
one step at a time.

1:06:55.277 --> 1:06:57.545
Where is he?

1:06:57.579 --> 1:06:59.248
Paul.

1:07:00.715 --> 1:07:03.251
You don't run. When you get
nervous, you don't run.

1:07:03.284 --> 1:07:05.520
How many times
do we have to go over this?

1:07:07.422 --> 1:07:09.257
I'll give you a minute.

1:07:12.561 --> 1:07:14.096
I'm sorry.

1:07:16.398 --> 1:07:19.601
No, I-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1:07:19.634 --> 1:07:21.536
Forget the school, okay?

1:07:21.570 --> 1:07:24.373
Forget the school.
It was a stupid idea.

1:07:25.539 --> 1:07:28.277
Okay?

1:07:28.309 --> 1:07:29.478
Yeah.

1:07:31.679 --> 1:07:34.715
I'm trying, pal.

1:07:34.748 --> 1:07:37.085
I'm trying as hard as I can.

1:07:37.119 --> 1:07:40.588
- I know. I'm trying, too.
- Yeah.

1:07:40.621 --> 1:07:42.590
I know you are.

1:07:42.623 --> 1:07:44.358
Where's your mask?

1:07:44.391 --> 1:07:46.861
- I lost it.
- Okay. That's okay.

1:07:46.894 --> 1:07:49.230
It doesn't matter.
We'll get you a new one.

1:07:49.264 --> 1:07:53.367
I was thinking maybe...
maybe it'd be easier

1:07:53.400 --> 1:07:55.403
- if I wore one, too, so we...
- No. No, Dad,

1:07:55.436 --> 1:07:58.106
it's... it's fine.

1:08:02.443 --> 1:08:04.880
Okay.

1:08:06.614 --> 1:08:07.782
Wow.

1:08:10.152 --> 1:08:12.487
You went to go find your mom.

1:08:14.688 --> 1:08:17.592
- How'd you know that?
- That... it doesn't matter.

1:08:18.627 --> 1:08:20.830
You still want to find her?

1:08:22.430 --> 1:08:25.267
You told me you didn't know
where she lived.

1:08:48.856 --> 1:08:51.659
- Okay.
- This is it?

1:08:51.693 --> 1:08:52.862
Yeah.

1:08:54.261 --> 1:08:57.231
Have you ever been in there?

1:08:57.265 --> 1:08:59.334
No. No.

1:08:59.367 --> 1:09:02.503
I mean, I've been through
her, uh, garbage a few times.

1:09:02.537 --> 1:09:06.375
Not in, like, a creepy sense
but in a professional way.

1:09:08.443 --> 1:09:11.713
It's funny, I always thought
she lived in, like...

1:09:11.746 --> 1:09:13.715
Paris or something.

1:09:13.747 --> 1:09:15.750
Paris. Nope.

1:09:18.552 --> 1:09:20.689
Are you sure you don't want me
to go in there with you?

1:09:20.721 --> 1:09:23.791
No. I'm okay.

1:09:23.824 --> 1:09:25.827
Okay.

1:09:36.371 --> 1:09:38.774
Paul, wait.

1:09:38.806 --> 1:09:40.975
I don't know what
it's gonna be like in there,

1:09:41.009 --> 1:09:44.246
okay, so I don't think you
should expect it go great.

1:09:44.279 --> 1:09:46.715
I know, Dad.

1:09:55.489 --> 1:09:57.358
And the last thing to ask,

1:09:57.391 --> 1:09:58.793
I guess...

1:10:05.899 --> 1:10:09.403
...did you ever wonder
if I would find you?

1:10:09.436 --> 1:10:11.439
Hi.

1:10:16.645 --> 1:10:18.647
Hello.

1:10:21.983 --> 1:10:26.654
I can get you, um,
some water, or, like, um...

1:10:26.688 --> 1:10:28.323
Water?

1:10:41.435 --> 1:10:43.904
I always thought
you lived in a mansion,

1:10:43.938 --> 1:10:47.643
with kids who played
the flute or the cello.

1:10:55.949 --> 1:10:57.818
Did you want me
to have a nice house

1:10:57.851 --> 1:11:00.822
so you could come
and stay with me?

1:11:00.854 --> 1:11:04.592
No, it just made it easier
to dislike you.

1:11:08.529 --> 1:11:13.034
Um, sorry to disappoint.

1:11:16.805 --> 1:11:20.643
I don't have a flute.
I have a recorder, I think.

1:11:21.810 --> 1:11:23.512
Do you want it?

1:11:23.545 --> 1:11:26.547
Okay.

1:11:26.581 --> 1:11:28.284
I think it's somewhere
over here.

1:11:34.823 --> 1:11:36.692
Yeah.

1:11:41.762 --> 1:11:44.300
Happy birthday.

1:11:46.600 --> 1:11:48.569
You remembered.

1:11:48.603 --> 1:11:50.605
Yeah.

1:11:52.940 --> 1:11:55.310
I don't know how to play this.

1:11:57.779 --> 1:11:59.614
Here. Want to show you.

1:11:59.646 --> 1:12:03.051
Just, um, put your fingers
over these holes like this.

1:12:16.730 --> 1:12:18.065
You're really bad at that.

1:12:18.099 --> 1:12:21.802
Yeah, let's be
honest, these things...

1:12:21.836 --> 1:12:25.539
sound like shit
no matter what, so...

1:12:25.573 --> 1:12:27.576
Damn it,
I was trying not to swear.

1:12:29.109 --> 1:12:31.512
I'm sorry. It's just...

1:12:44.893 --> 1:12:46.427
It was me.

1:12:50.664 --> 1:12:53.534
I never told your dad, but...

1:12:56.537 --> 1:12:58.706
...this is pretty much
all my fault.

1:12:59.740 --> 1:13:01.743
What do you mean?

1:13:11.586 --> 1:13:13.422
Dad?

1:13:13.454 --> 1:13:14.989
Who's that?

1:13:15.023 --> 1:13:17.926
- It's me.
- Sleeping.

1:13:21.662 --> 1:13:24.532
Remember the person
I told you about last night?

1:13:27.902 --> 1:13:29.904
He's here.

1:13:39.113 --> 1:13:41.516
Well, would you look at that.

1:13:41.548 --> 1:13:45.921
Jen, uh, you mind
leaving us alone for a bit?

1:14:20.121 --> 1:14:23.658
You know, I was awful angry
when she told me about you.

1:14:23.690 --> 1:14:26.661
If I had known before,
I-I would've...

1:14:26.694 --> 1:14:28.830
I mean, I didn't even know
she had a kid.

1:14:28.863 --> 1:14:31.099
You didn't know about me?

1:14:31.131 --> 1:14:34.935
She's always been very, uh...

1:14:34.969 --> 1:14:38.640
It was hard for her,
growing up with me.

1:14:38.672 --> 1:14:41.643
Used to lie and say
that her dad was the guy

1:14:41.676 --> 1:14:44.513
who hosted "Wheel of Fortune."

1:14:44.546 --> 1:14:46.548
Yeah, she pretty much
cut me out of her life

1:14:46.581 --> 1:14:48.884
for something like 25 years.

1:14:48.917 --> 1:14:51.553
When did she start
talking to you again?

1:14:51.586 --> 1:14:54.289
Uh, about 13 years ago.

